{
  "texts": [
    "The second row is the same, but for the treatments below the threshold (the rest).",
    "Odds ratio is a sum of the first row divided by the sum of the second row.",
    "It estimates the likelihood of observing the treatment with the same MoA or pathway in the top connections.",
    "We calculate the odds ratio of each individual query, and then obtain the average over all query treatments.",
    "The threshold we use is 1% of connections, meaning we expect the top 1% of matching results in the list to be significantly enriched for positive matches."
  ]
}